span.span: Basic process flow for simple demo which writes WAV files to the SD card.
Audio buffers are filled via DMA, not shown here.
This diagram represents a simplified high level view of the process, some details are omitted.
A file is done when enough buffers have been written to the SD card to fill up the allotted time.
This process is valid for early demos only, the final application will determine file start and stop times via RTC interrupts.
